===============================================
MongoDB is one of the popular NoSQL database.
Tables are called as Collections or document.
Records are stored in the below formats
Array:
index value
ex: [ "technology",
      "Programming",
      "Web development"]

Embedded document
Ex:
 Ex. {"name ": "Surendiran",
       "Email ": "surendiranveda@gmail.com"
     }
Array of Embedded document
[{"name ": "Surendiran",
       "Email ": "surendiranveda@gmail.com"
     }
{"name ": "Sangeetha",
       "Email ": "Sangeethaveda@gmail.com"
     }
]
Nested Embedded document
Ex:
[
{"user": "User1",
"comment":"Great post",
"replies":{"name ": "Surendiran","Email ": "surendiranveda@gmail.com"}
          {"name ": "Sangeetha", "Email ": "Sangeethaveda@gmail.com"}
}
]

ctrl+Enter => to enter the data continuously

use shop => to create database
db.products.inserOne() => To create new collection and document
db.products.find() => To display all the records from the document
db.products.findone() => To display first one record
show dbs => show all the database
db.products.insertMany([])
db.products.find({"details,name":"Samsung"})
db.products.updateOne({name:"Samsung"},{$set:{"price":50}})
db.product.updateMany({})
db.product.deleteOne({name:"Samsung"})
db.product.deleteMany({name:"Samsung"})







